quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,20,"O believers! Obey Allah and his Messenger and do not turn your back to him, now that you have heard all"
  8,21,"Do not be like those who say: \"We hear,\" but give no heed to what they hear"
  8,22,For the worst animals in the sight of Allah are those deaf and dumb people who do not use common sense
  8,23,"Had Allah perceived any virtue in them He would have indeed endowed them with hearing. Had he made them (those without virtue) hear, they would have turned away and refused to listen"
  8,24,"O believers! Respond to the call of Allah and His Messenger, when He calls you to that which gives you life; and know that Allah stands between man and his heart, and that it is He in Whose presence you shall all be assembled"
  8,25,Guard yourselves against temptation. The wrongdoers among you are not the only ones who will be tempted; and know that Allah is strict in retribution
  8,26,"Call to mind how He gave you shelter when you were a few in number and were oppressed in the land, ever fearing lest the enemy would kidnap you. He made you strong with His help and provided you a safe asylum and gave you pure things for sustenance so that you may give thanks"
  8,27,"O believers! Do not betray the trust of Allah and His Messenger, nor violate your trusts knowingly"
  8,28,"You should know that your wealth and your children are, in fact, a test for you, and that Allah is He with Whom is your mighty reward"